不要跑
Don't run.

12
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:06,137
这是皮瑞拉帕帝的家吗？
(SPEAKlNG FRENCH)
ls this the property of Perrier LaPadite?

13
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:07,671
我就是皮瑞拉帕帝
l am Perrier LaPadite.

14
00:04:09,048 --> 00:04:12,142
幸会了，拉帕帝先生...
lt is a pleasure to meet you,
Monsieur LaPadite...

15
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:14,687
...我是纳粹党卫军汉斯蓝达上校
...l am Colonel Hans Landa of the SS.

16
00:04:15,221 --> 00:04:16,245
我能为你做什么？
What can l do for you?

17
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:19,656
请我进去你家...
l was hoping you could invite me
inside your home...

18
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:22,190
...咱们俩一起谈谈
...and we may have a discussion.

19
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:25,153
没问题，请吧
Certainly. After you.

20
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,936
蓝达上校，这是我的家人
Colonel Landa, this is my family.

21
00:04:47,086 --> 00:04:48,348
我是纳粹党卫军汉斯蓝达上校...
Colonel Hans Landa of the SS...

22
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:49,847
...小姐们...
...Mademoiselle...

23
00:04:49,922 --> 00:04:51,184
...我随时效劳
...at your service.

24
00:04:52,091 --> 00:04:56,289
关于你们家的谣言是真的
The rumors l have heard in the
village about your family are all true.

25
00:04:59,565 --> 00:05:02,227
你的女儿一个比一个漂亮
Each one of your daughters
is more lovely than the last.

26
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:04,994
谢谢
Merci.

27
00:05:05,738 --> 00:05:06,762
来...
Please...

28
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:08,564
...请坐
...have a seat.

29
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:16,214
苏珊，替上校倒杯酒
Suzanne, would you be so good as to
get the Colonel some wine?

30
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,708
不
But no.

31
00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:21,149
谢谢你，但是我不喝酒
Merci beaucoup, Monsieur LaPadite,
but no wine.

32
00:05:22,221 --> 00:05:27,056
这是酪农场
你家应该有牛奶吧？
This being a dairy farm, one would be
safe in assuming you have milk?

33
00:05:27,126 --> 00:05:28,218
对
Oui.

34
00:05:28,294 --> 00:05:29,659
那就来杯牛奶吧
Then milk is what l prefer.

35
00:05:30,063 --> 00:05:31,121
好的
Very well.

36
00:05:32,265 --> 00:05:33,926
茱莉，请你关上窗户
Julie, would you mind closing the window?

37
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:55,947
谢谢你
Merci.

38
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:15,339
我要对你家人和你的乳牛...
Monsieur, to both your family
and your cows...

39
00:06:16,642 --> 00:06:18,109
...说声：  “好极了”
...l say, ''Bravo.''

40
00:06:19,178 --> 00:06:20,202
谢谢你
Thank you.

41
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:24,278
一起过来坐
Please Join me at your table.

42
00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:26,175
好的
Very well.

43
00:06:31,691 --> 00:06:32,715
拉帕帝先生...
Monsieur LaPadite...

44
00:06:33,526 --> 00:06:37,724
...我们要谈的事最好私下谈
...what we have to discuss
would be better discussed in private.

45
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:41,499
我请手下在外面等
You'll notice l left my men outdoors.

46
00:06:42,635 --> 00:06:47,504
不介意的话，请小姐们出去
lf it wouldn't offend them, could you
ask your lovely ladies to step outside?

47
00:06:49,308 --> 00:06:50,332
说得对
You are right.

48
00:06:51,344 --> 00:06:53,505
夏绿蒂，带她们出去
Charlotte, would you take the girls
outside?

49
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,970
我和上校有话要谈
The Colonel and l need to have
a few words.

50
00:07:08,027 --> 00:07:09,187
拉帕帝先生...
Monsieur LaPadite...

51
00:07:10,863 --> 00:07:15,596
...很抱歉，我会的法文都讲光了
...l regret to inform you
l've exhausted the extent of my French.

52
00:07:16,903 --> 00:07:20,669
勉强讲下去只会让我很糗
To continue to speak it so inadequately
would only serve to embarrass me.

53
00:07:20,907 --> 00:07:24,741
但是听说你的英文说得很溜
However, l've been led to believe
you speak English quite well.

54
00:07:26,078 --> 00:07:27,102
是的
Yes.

55
00:07:27,213 --> 00:07:31,377
我也是，那么客随主便...
Well, it Just so happens, l do as well.
This being your house...

56
00:07:31,684 --> 00:07:35,916
...请你让我用英文继续说下去
...l ask your permission to switch
to English...
...for the remainder of the conversation.

57
00:07:37,223 --> 00:07:38,247
请便
By all means.

58
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:41,754
我对你和你家人很熟悉
While l'm very familiar
with you and your family,

59
00:07:41,861 --> 00:07:45,524
但我不知道你对我熟不熟悉
l have no way of knowing
if you are familiar with who l am.

60
00:07:46,432 --> 00:07:48,627
你知道有我这个人吗？
Are you aware of my existence?

61
00:07:49,702 --> 00:07:51,863
-知道
-非常好
-Yes.
-This is good.

62
00:07:52,438 --> 00:07:56,465
你知道我在法国的任务吗？
Now, are you aware of the Job l've been
ordered to carry out in France?

63
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:00,369
知道
Yes.

64
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:02,571
请告诉我你听说什么
Please tell me what you've heard.

65
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:09,718
我听说元首命令你捕杀
仍在法国的犹太人
l've heard
that the Fuhrer has put you in charge
of rounding up the Jews left in France

66
00:08:09,789 --> 00:08:12,724
他们不是躲起来
就是假装成非犹太人
who are either hiding or passing for Gentile.

67
00:08:14,126 --> 00:08:17,061
就连元首都没你说得好
The Fuhrer couldn't have
said it better himself.

68
00:08:18,965 --> 00:08:22,628
虽然我很欢迎你来访
But the meaning of your visit,

69
00:08:23,102 --> 00:08:27,300
但是却不知道原因
pleasant though it is, is mysterious to me.

70
00:08:28,941 --> 00:08:32,240
德军九个月前来搜过我家
The Germans looked through my house
nine months ago for hiding Jews

71
00:08:32,311 --> 00:08:34,211
什么也没找到
and found nothing.

72
00:08:35,748 --> 00:08:37,409
我知道
l'm aware of that.

73
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:40,341
我看过报告
l've read the reports of this area.

74
00:08:42,421 --> 00:08:45,618
但是就像每个新官上任的公司
But like any enterprise,
when under new management,

75
00:08:45,691 --> 00:08:48,785
同样的事得再做一次
there is always
a slight duplication of efforts,

76
00:08:49,996 --> 00:08:54,660
大部分是浪费时间
但还是非做不可
most of it being a complete waste of time,
but needs to be done nevertheless.

77
00:08:55,668 --> 00:08:58,762
我只想请教一些问题
l Just have a few questions,
monSieur LaPadite.

78
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:02,504
你只要照实回答
lf you can assist me with answers,

79
00:09:02,608 --> 00:09:05,668
你家的档案就能结案
my department can close
the file on your family.

80
00:09:14,153 --> 00:09:15,848
是这样的
Now,

81
00:09:16,989 --> 00:09:21,289
法国被占领之前
这地区有四家犹太人
before the occupation,
there were four Jewish families in this area,

82
00:09:21,827 --> 00:09:24,159
全都跟你一样是酪农
all dairy farmers like yourself.

83
00:09:25,998 --> 00:09:30,628
德勒列克、罗伦昂、拉维特
Doleracs, Rollins, the Loveitts

84
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:34,168
以及德瑞芙斯
and the Dreyfuses.

85
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,832
对吧？
ls that correct?

86
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:36,966
就我所知
To my knowledge,

87
00:09:37,043 --> 00:09:40,501
他们是犹太裔的酪农
those were the Jewish families
among the dairy farmers.

88
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:44,480
上校，介意我抽烟斗吗？
Herr Colonel,
would it disturb you if l smoked my pipe?

89
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:46,017
请便，拉帕帝先生
(CHUCKLES) Please,
monSieur LaPadite,

90
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:49,054
这是你家，自在一点
this is your house,
make yourself comfortable.

91
00:09:49,388 --> 00:09:52,357
根据这些文件
Now, according to these papers,

92
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:56,717
这地区的犹太家庭都被拘捕
all the Jewish families
in this area have been accounted for

93
00:09:56,829 --> 00:09:59,662
除了德瑞芙斯一家人
except the Dreyfuses.

94
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:04,525
看来他们去年突然消失无踪
Somewhere in the last year
it would appear they've vanished.

95
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:07,903
我猜他们不是逃亡成功
Which leads me to the conclusion
that they've either made good their escape

96
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:10,874
就是有人把他们藏得很好
or someone
is very successfully hiding them.

97
00:10:12,078 --> 00:10:15,707
你听过德瑞芙斯一家的事吗？
What have you heard about
the Dreyfuses, monSieur LaPadite?

98
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:18,215
-只有谣言
-我最爱谣言了！
-Only rumors.
-l love rumors!

99
00:10:19,719 --> 00:10:21,118
事实很容易误导我们
Facts could be so misleading,

100
00:10:21,187 --> 00:10:24,350
谣言不管真假都能泄密
where rumors, true or false,
are often revealing.

101
00:10:24,724 --> 00:10:26,214
所以，拉帕帝先生
So, monSieur LaPadite,

102
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:29,557
你听过德瑞芙斯一家什么谣言？
what rumors have you heard
regarding the Dreyfuses?

103
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:35,529
我说过，这只是个谣言
Again, this is Just a rumor,

104
00:10:35,601 --> 00:10:41,904
我们听说德瑞芙斯一家
逃到西班牙了
but we heard the Dreyfuses
had made their way into Spain.

105
00:10:49,749 --> 00:10:52,616
你听到他们逃亡的谣言？
So, the rumors you've heard
have been of escape?

106
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,710
对
Yes.

107
00:10:58,824 --> 00:11:02,624
虽然你没见过德瑞芙斯一家
Having never met the Dreyfuses,
would you confirm for me

108
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:05,959
但是请你说出他们全家的名字
the exact members of the household
and their names?

109
00:11:11,437 --> 00:11:13,405
他们家有五个人
There were five of them.

110
00:11:15,608 --> 00:11:18,270
父亲，雅各
The father, Jacob.

111
00:11:20,112 --> 00:11:22,603
太太，米兰
Wife, Miram.

112
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:28,279
还有她的兄弟
巴布
And her brother, Bob.

113
00:11:35,494 --> 00:11:37,257
巴布几岁？
How old is Bob?

114
00:11:38,664 --> 00:11:40,564
30、31岁
Thirty, 31 .

115
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:45,793
继续说
Continue.

116
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:47,498
孩子们
And the children,

117
00:11:49,275 --> 00:11:50,902
艾莫斯
Amos

118
00:11:52,478 --> 00:11:54,241
还有苏珊娜
and Shosanna.

119
00:11:56,115 --> 00:11:58,015
孩子们几岁？
Ages of the children?

120
00:12:04,990 --> 00:12:08,551
艾莫斯，9或10岁
Amos was nine or 10.

121
00:12:11,464 --> 00:12:14,956
-苏珊娜呢？
-苏珊娜是
-And Shosanna?
-And Shosanna was

122
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:20,369
18或19岁
我不是很确定
18 or 19. l'm not really sure.

123
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,582
我猜我问完了
Well, l guess that should do it.

124
00:12:40,025 --> 00:12:44,394
不过我走之前
能不能再来杯好喝的牛奶？
However, before l go, could l have
another glass of your delicious milk?

125
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,128
当然可以
But of course.

126
00:12:55,741 --> 00:12:57,732
拉帕帝先生
MonSieur LaPadite,

127
00:12:57,810 --> 00:13:01,803
你知道法国人替我取的绰号吗？
are you aware of the nickname
the people of France have given me?

128
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:07,919
我对这种事没兴趣
l have no interest in such things.

129
00:13:08,921 --> 00:13:11,617
但是你知道他们怎么叫我
But you are aware of what they call me.

130
00:13:14,226 --> 00:13:15,853
我知道
l'm aware.

131
00:13:17,263 --> 00:13:19,128
你知道什么？
What are you aware of?

132
00:13:29,074 --> 00:13:32,237
-他们叫你“犹太人终结者”
-没错
-That they call you ''The Jew Hunter.''
-Precisely.

133
00:13:34,513 --> 00:13:37,175
我了解你很怕说出这个绰号
l understand your trepidation in repeating it.

134
00:13:37,283 --> 00:13:39,581
海德利希很讨厌
Heydrich apparently hates the moniker

135
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,280
布拉格人替他取的绰号
the good people of Prague
have bestowed on him.

136
00:13:42,354 --> 00:13:45,619
但是我不t他怎么会讨厌
“刽子手”这绰号
Actually, why he would hate the name
''the Hangman'' is baffling to me.

137
00:13:45,691 --> 00:13:49,092
这绰号一定是他尽全力得到的
lt would appear he has done
everything in his power to earn it.

138
00:13:49,161 --> 00:13:52,426
我不同，我特爱我的绰号
Now l, on the other hand,
love my unofficial title

139
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,864
尤其是我努力挣来的
precisely because l've earned it.

140
00:13:56,302 --> 00:14:00,363
这代表跟其他德国军人比起来
The feature that makes me
such an effective hunter of the Jews is,

141
00:14:00,472 --> 00:14:03,134
我猎杀犹太人的效率超高
as opposed to most German soldiers,

142
00:14:03,209 --> 00:14:05,200
我会像犹太人思考
l can think like a Jew

143
00:14:05,878 --> 00:14:08,608
他们只会像德国人思考
where they can only think like a German.

144
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:11,715
更精准地说，是德国士兵
(CHUCKLlNG) More precisely,
a German soldier.

145
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:23,026
若要以一种动物形容德国人
Now, if one were to determine what attribute
the German people share with a beast,

146
00:14:23,562 --> 00:14:27,123
那就是狡猾掠杀的隼鹰
it would be the cunning
and the predatory instinct of a hawk.

147
00:14:27,566 --> 00:14:31,468
若要以一种动物形容犹太人
But if one were to determine what attributes
the Jews share with a beast,

148
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:33,630
那就是老鼠
it would be that of the rat.

149
00:14:36,408 --> 00:14:40,310
元首和戈培尔的宣传部
也这么形容犹太人
The Fuhrer and Goebbels' propaganda
have said pretty much the same thing.

150
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:43,371
但是我们的结论不同
But where our conclusions differ,

151
00:14:43,482 --> 00:14:46,474
我不认为比较两者是种羞辱
is l don't consider the comparison an insult.

152
00:14:48,988 --> 00:14:52,822
想一想老鼠生活的世界
Consider for a moment
the world a rat lives in.

153
00:14:53,692 --> 00:14:55,887
那是充满敌意的世界
lt's a hostile world, indeed.

154
00:14:56,729 --> 00:15:00,165
假设现在有只老鼠从门前窜过
lf a rat were to scamper
through your front door, right now,

155
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:02,666
你会对它有敌意吗？
would you greet it with hostility?

156
00:15:03,602 --> 00:15:05,502
我猜会吧
l suppose l would.

157
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:10,508
老鼠曾经做了什么
让你对它们充满敌意？
Has a rat ever done anything to you to create
this animosity you feel toward them?

158
00:15:11,377 --> 00:15:14,005
老鼠会散布疾病，还会咬人
Rats spread disease. They bite people.

159
00:15:14,546 --> 00:15:18,346
老鼠的确散播过瘟疫
不过那是很久以前的事
Rats were the cause of the bubonic plague,
but that's some time ago.

160
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:23,621
让我告诉你
松鼠也能散布老鼠散布的疾病
l propose to you any disease
a rat could spread,
a squirrel could equally carry.

161
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:25,452
你同意吗？
Would you agree?

162
00:15:27,126 --> 00:15:29,720
但是你对松鼠却没有
Yet, l assume you don't share
the same animosity with squirrels

163
00:15:29,795 --> 00:15:32,559
-对老鼠的敌意，对吧？
-对
-that you do with rats, do you?
-No.

164
00:15:33,032 --> 00:15:35,523
但它们都是啮齿动物呀
Yet, they're both rodents, are they not?

165
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:39,560
除了尾巴，它们长得挺像的
And except for the tail,
they even rather look alike, don't they?

166
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:42,805
这想法真有趣，上校
lt's an interesting thought, Herr Colonel.

167
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:45,567
不管这想法是多么有趣
However interesting as the thought may be,

168
00:15:45,644 --> 00:15:48,909
你对老鼠的看法不会不一样
it makes not one bit of difference
to how you feel.

169
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:55,311
要是有一只老鼠跑进来
lf a rat were to walk in here, right now,
as l'm talking

170
00:15:56,455 --> 00:16:00,323
你会替它准备一碟牛奶吗？
would you greet it with a saucer
of your delicious milk?

171
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:02,189
大概不会吧
Probably not.

172
00:16:02,561 --> 00:16:04,222
我就知道
l didn't think so.

173
00:16:04,830 --> 00:16:06,388
你不喜欢老鼠
You don't like them.

